T​he Art of Negotiation is a highly significant and valuable course. It has mentioned skills and tactics how to do a successful negotiations. The videos of Instructor Ms Sue Robins is highly interactive and is full of knowledge and informations; Wonderful Lectures. The course taught me: How to prepare for negotiation, reserach your counterpart, place and timing, power, perceived power, confidence, power of listening without any prejudgements, silence, persuasion,  BATNA (Best Alternative Tool for the Negotiated Agreement), how to be polite during a conflicting situation and principled negotiation, building trust; these are significantly important points to be kept in mind while doing the negotiations. negotiation. It has improved my understaning of Negotiation. When I was talking to my father about a Rent dispute, as our tenet was creating problems while vacating our house. The knowledge gained from this course made my negotiations with my father and tenet more meaningful and find SMART (Specific, measurable, assertive, rational and time bound) ways and logical reasoning to negotiate. I'm highly satisfied with this valuable course offered through Coursera. Thank you so much Ms Sue Robins and Coursera for giving me this wonderful opportunity to learn "The Art of Negotiation".
